&lt;p&gt;Make Wayve the experience that defines your career!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Global Logistics Manager is a critical leadership role responsible for defining, executing, and optimizing Wayve’s global logistics, customs, transportation, and potentially warehousing operations across the UK, US, Asia Pacific, and EU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns end-to-end inbound and outbound logistics, customs compliance, tariffs and duties, transportation strategy, and logistics partner management. The ideal candidate is a strategic, hands-on leader who can operate in a fast-moving, hardware-driven environment, balancing speed, cost, compliance, and risk while enabling critical program milestones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will have help setting up the logistics roadmap as Wayve continue to scale up internationally&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute a global logistics strategy aligned with company objectives, hardware programs, and regional growth plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own relationships with global and regional freight forwarders, carriers, and customs brokers and lead rate negotiations, contract renewals, and capacity planning across regions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and ensure full compliance with domestic and international trade regulations, customs rules, tariff/duty, and safety standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and implement logistics-related processes and tools and ensure they are documented, standardized, and scalable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure seamless integration between logistics systems and purchasing, warehouse, finance, and other stakeholders workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to set you up for success as a Logistics Manager at Wayve, we’re looking for the following skills and experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prefer to have managerial experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience to set up company logistics strategy and team from scratch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of carrier/forwarder shipping rate and cost breakdown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of international custom/duty/tariff regulation and policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working at both a startup and established company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automotive background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;15+ years of experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
