&lt;p&gt;As Wayve rapidly scales, our IT team plays a crucial role in keeping our employees productive and our operations efficient. We’re looking for an IT Support Engineer (TC2) to support the day-to-day IT needs across our Japan offices. This is a full-time, on-site role, with flexibility required to support each of our 3 offices as needed. You’ll be a hands-on, first-line problem solver—supporting everything from laptop configuration to meeting room A/V to network troubleshooting. You’ll also support joiner/mover/leaver processes, including onboarding and off-boarding tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone early in their IT career who is eager to learn, thrives in a fast-paced environment, and wants to grow their skills while contributing to cutting-edge work in autonomous vehicle development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End-User Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide timely support for laptops (Windows, macOS, Linux), mobile devices, printers, and peripherals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot hardware and software issues and escalate as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage onboarding and off-boarding tasks, including account provisioning and hardware setup when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IT Systems &amp;amp; Tools&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and monitor endpoint management systems (e.g., MDM, patching, asset inventory).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in configuring and maintaining core business tools (e.g., GSuite, Slack, Jira, …).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help with access control and identity systems (SSO, MFA, user permissions).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network &amp;amp; Infrastructure Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support basic network troubleshooting (Wi-Fi, VPN, wired connectivity) under the guidance of senior engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage and maintain meeting room A/V equipment, including Google Meet and Teams rooms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide on-site support across Japan offices as needed (3 offices).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; Process&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to internal IT documentation and knowledge base articles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log and track tickets using the internal IT ticketing system (e.g., Jira, ServiceNow).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with IT, Security, and Facilities teams to ensure smooth daily operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help support company-wide IT initiatives and system rollouts as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to set you up for success as an IT Support Engineer at Wayve, we’re looking for the following skills and experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years + of professional experience in an IT support or systems administration role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with macOS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathetic and service-oriented with strong communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn and grow in a rapidly evolving tech environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize tasks and follow through with minimal supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to identity platforms (e.g., Okta, Google Workspace, Azure AD).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with ticketing systems and ITSM workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JLPT N1 required (or equivalent business-level fluency) in Japanese, written and spoken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English (written and spoken) required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desirable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of networking concepts (IP, DNS, DHCP, VPN).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Linux operating systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with endpoint management tools (e.g., Kandji, Intune, …).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
